{
  "texts": [
    "Instead, we illustrate all the necessary concepts using this example, and use this DAG for multiple possible causal questions.",
    "For a particular study, it might be best to construct a particular DAG for the specific causal question.",
    "A reasonable starting point for constructing a DAG for a particular causal question of 𝑋 on 𝑌 might be the following: (1) consider all factors that affect and are affected by 𝑋 and/or 𝑌; (2) consider how these factors are causally related between each other.",
    "There might be additional relevant considerations, but it should provide a reasonable simplification to start with.",
    "A useful tool for working with DAGs is called dagitty (Textor et al., 2016), which is available from the website http://dagitty.net, which also contains many useful pointers to additional introductions and tutorials."
  ]
}